I"v<p>This short tutorial will show you how to create custom bullet points without using the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">list-style-image</code> CSS property. <!--break--></p>

<ol>
  <li>set <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">list-style-type</code> of ul to ‘none’
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>ul {
 list-style-type: none;
}
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Create ::before pseudo-element for li. These properties are compulsory!
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>li::before {
 content: "\f005";
 font-family: "Font Awesome 5 Free";
}
</code></pre></div>    </div>
    <p>3.
```
li {
 // Optional properties
 padding-right: 8px;
 color: yellow;
 font-weight: 600;
}</p>
  </li>
</ol>

